{"id":"1503.07145","submitter":"Basak Gurel","authors":"Viktor L. Ginzburg, Basak Z. Gurel","title":"Non-contractible Periodic Orbits in Hamiltonian Dynamics on Closed\n  Symplectic Manifolds","comments":"24 pages; minor revisions made, references added; to appear in\n  Compositio Mathematica","journal-ref":"Compositio Math. 152 (2016) 1777-1799","doi":"10.1112/S0010437X16007508","report-no":null,"categories":"math.SG math.DS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We study Hamiltonian diffeomorphisms of closed symplectic manifolds with\nnon-contractible periodic orbits. In a variety of settings, we show that the\npresence of one non-contractible periodic orbit of a Hamiltonian diffeomorphism\nof a closed toroidally monotone or toroidally negative monotone symplectic\nmanifold implies the existence of infinitely many non-contractible periodic\norbits in a specific collection of free homotopy classes. The main new\ningredient in the proofs of these results is a filtration of Floer homology by\nthe so-called augmented action. This action is independent of capping, and,\nunder favorable conditions, the augmented action filtration for toroidally\n(negative) monotone manifolds can play the same role as the ordinary action\nfiltration for atoroidal manifolds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Mar 2015 19:25:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 8 Mar 2016 06:34:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-20"}
